Theressa has been the most exceptional caregiver for my sister Carol who has an increasingly disabling condition. She is loving and really knows Carol through observation and sensitivity. This has been especially meaningful  as my sister loses her ability to speak. Theressa is very clear on allowing her autonomy wherever possible. At the same time she knows the medical needs, works closely and carefully with the facilities staff, never misses a beat. We are so grateful for the years of care she has provided.
Your kindness, skill, and patience are amazing. The loving and steady and reliable care are the absolute best. Our family is so lucky that you can care for Carol.

Hello Friends at Care Heros,

My sister Carol is truly blessed by the care Theressa Collins provides for her. Theressa has cared for Carol for 7 years, as her Parkinson’s Disease has progressed.

Theressa is is an extremely competent caregiver, attentive to Carol’s needs, and working well with facility staff, co-workers, and family. She is patient, scrupulously attentive to detail, and attuned  to Carol’s physical and emotional well being, as well to her basic physical care.

These past couple of years, Theressa has seen Carol through a number of particular challenges, including the loss of our father, who lived in the same residence, all the restrictions and extra confinement necessitated by Covid, and a move from her Assisted Living apartment to the Skilled Nursing floor, as well as the ever increasing challenges of PD, including cognitive slowness and difficulty speaking and being understood. In light of this, Carol has had sometimes had big emotions, and has lashed out at Theressa. Despite this, Theressa has responded calmly and gently as well as with firmness. 

Theressa respects Carol’s need for personal space, quiet times, and treats Carol with the dignity she deserves.

Theressa works well with her supervisor and coworkers, with facility staff, and with family, sharing her observations and experience of Carol to help us all provide the most appropriate, respectful and loving care so Carol have a good quality of life within the limitations and challenges of her disability.

Before Covid I was in the habit of visiting family in Chicago for several days every 2-3 months,  and have gotten to see Theressa with Carol on those visits. That was, of course suspended in the era of Covid, when my visits have been weekly on Zoom, with Theressa’s help. I have now resumed regular visits as well as Zoom sessions. I recently had the opportunity to visit Carol for a week, welcoming her and her daytime caregivers to an AirBnB apartment during the days to give her a change of scene and a more homelike environment with family. I got the chance to observe Theressa closely; as always, she struck just the right tone between being helpful and giving space. Theressa is an outstanding caregiver, and she has come to feel like family to Carol, and me, our other sister, and our family as a whole. She truly cares about Carol and has a loving and compassionate heart, and a solid faith which is palpable. I am most grateful for the gift of her in Carol’s and the family’s life.

Sincerely,

Sarah Farley	
(Carol’s sister)
